Asparagus Bacon Cheesy Quiche

1/4 lb thick cut bacon, chopped
1 spring onion, chopped
salt and pepper to taste
1/2 c thinly sliced asparagus
6 eggs
1/2 c half and half
3/4 c shredded gruyere
1 9" pie crust

Preheat oven to 375F. In medium saucepan over medium heat, coot bacon until crisp and fat has rendered out. Add onion and season with salt to taste. Cook until soft, then add asparagus. Cook until asparagus is bright green, ~1 min, then remove from heat. Cool slightly. In a medium bowl, whisk eggs and half and half; add salt and pepper to taste. Place pice crust into a 9" pie tin, scoop asparagus mixture into the bottom and spread evenly. Add egg mixture; sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 40-45 min, or until golden brown and just set.


pie crust:
2 tbsp white distilled vinegar
2 tbsp vodka
1/3 c ice cold water
ice for chilling
2 1/2 c ap flour
1 tbsp sugar
1 tsp salt
1/2 c shortening, chilled, and cut into 1/2" pieces
1/2 c (1 stick) unsalted butter, chilled and cut into 1/2" cubes

In a small liquid measuring cup, combine vinegar, vodka, and water. Fill with ice and chill until ready to use. In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, and salt. Add the shortening and use a pastry cutter to cut the fat into the flour, creating cornmeal sized pieces. Add the butter and cut into the flour until mixtgure resembles a coarse meal, with a few pea sized butter pieces. Pour 1/4 c of the liquid over the flour and stir with a fork. Add another 3-6 tbsp of liquidm and with your fingertips, briefly mix into a shaggy dough. Divide the dough in half. Gather one half into a loose ball and wrap in plastic wrap, tuck and seal into a smooth 4" disc; repeat with second. Chill in the fridge for at least 1 hr or up to 3 days. Dough can be frozen for up to 1 month.
